Free Lunches
This doesn=E2=80=99t mean that venture capitalists are smarter than anyone =
else. As I mentioned earlier, they=E2=80=99re wrong a lot.=C2=A0
What it does mean is that venture capital, with its Power Laws, is the asse=
t class best designed to embrace variance.=20
Would returns look better if VCs simply funded the good companies and didn=
=E2=80=99t fund the bad ones? Maybe in the short-term, maybe not in the lon=
g-term, but it=E2=80=99s a moot point, because no one knows what the great =
ones are going to be ahead of time. Venture is beautiful for embracing that=
=2E=C2=A0
Venture capitalists can fund the wildest ideas in the world, many of which =
won=E2=80=99t work, some of which will work bigly, and their returns as a g=
roup end up being pretty great.=C2=A0
And on top of that, we get the fruits of innovation, because venture capita=
l is the only asset class that funds truly new things.=C2=A0
Take the current hype cycle in AI. Venture capitalists are pouring stomach =
churning amounts of money into foundation model companies. Billions of whic=
h will, for all intents and purposes, be lit on fire. The problem is: it=E2=
=80=99s hard to tell which billions until you put the money up and watch it=
 play out. Venture capital is designed to put those chips on the table and =
see what happens.=C2=A0
If history is a guide, most AI companies will go to zero, and a small handf=
ul will generate enough returns to carry the rest. Those returns will go to=
