sons.=C2=A0
VCs make money (and sometimes take credit) when other people =E2=80=93 foun=
ders and startup employees =E2=80=93 do all of the hard work. They have to =
tell founders =E2=80=9Cno, we don=E2=80=99t want to fund your life=E2=80=99=
s work=E2=80=9D much more often than they get to say =E2=80=9Cyes.=E2=80=9D=
 They invest in brash, risky companies that occasionally fail spectacularly=
=2E They jump from industry to industry=
 with, often, nowhere near the depth o=
f understanding of those industries as the people who work in them. They wr=
ite blogs and host podcasts =F0=9F=98=AC
And some of them are genuinely shitty: either bad investors or worse, as pr=
edatory behavior in the downturn exposed once again. They stand in the way =
of acquisitions [ https://substack.com/redirect/53afebf0-aec2-43b7-bed2-c8f=
8c2f2e622?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNp=
U ] that would be life-changing for founders but meaningless for returns. O=
